number of newspapers per hour. Machine B started printing earlier at a rate of 75 copies per hour. After Machine B had printed for 10 hours. Machine A had printed 340 copies. After Machine B had printed for 16 hours, Machine A had printed 886 copies.<br>(a) How many copies of newspapers did Machine A print per hour ? <br>(b) How long would Machine B have worked when both machines have printed a total of 2 750 copies ?','ms','2023-07-03 00:00:00','','Rosyth 2010 SA2','6.1.3.1','A'),(380,'MA_P6','A tour bus which left Kuala Lumphur at 10.30 a.m. was scheduled to reach Singapore by 5 p.m. After travelling for 2 hours at its usual speed, the bus stopped for 30 minutes due to some problems. In order to reach Singapore punctually, the bus increased its speed by 8.5 km/h. Given the bus took 4 hours to complete the rest of journey, find the distance between Kuala Lumphur and Singapore.','ms','2023-07-03 00:00:00','','Rosyth 2010 SA2','6.1.4.1','A'),(381,'MA_P6','Xavier, Yati and Zul each had a certain number of stamps. Af first, Yati had 200 stamps more than Xavier, and Zul had <math><mfrac><msup>3</msup><msup>4</msup></mfrac></math> the number of stamps Yati had. After Yati gave away <math><mfrac><msup>1</msup><msup>8</msup></mfrac></math> of her stamps to Xavier, she had 60 fewer stamps than Xavier.<br>What was the ratio of the number of stamps Xavier had to the number of stampes Yati had to the number of stamps Zul had at first? Give the answer in the simplest form.','ms','2023-07-03 00:00:00','','Rosyth 2010 SA2','6.1.3.1','A');
